latestPosts.caption:
Posted @withregram • @bridestodayin Our digital cover star, Karishma Tanna Bangera (@karishmaktanna) tied the knot with Mumbai-based businessman, Varun Bangera on February 5, 2022. But marriage is a lot more than having a magnificent wedding. It requires love, understanding, wisdom, and a lot more.

In conversation with Brides Today, Tanna talks about her love language, her conflict style, and the journey she embarked on to find her dream lehenga.

Read excerpts from the cover interview:

“My definition of love has evolved over the years. Earlier, it used to be about passion and excitement. Now, it’s more about understanding, support, and a deep emotional connection,” she adds, “I do believe in soulmates, but I’m not sure about love at first sight. I think it’s possible to have a strong connection with someone right away, but true love often develops and deepens over time.”

We’re on the hunt for Design Interns to join the core team of a celebrity-led western wear label that blends effortless glam with everyday edge.

What You’ll Do:
✨ Assist in creating mood boards, tech packs & sample development
✨ Support design research – trends, silhouettes, fabrics, trims
✨ Be part of fittings, production meetings & shoot prep
✨ Work closely with the core creative & production teams
✨ Gain hands-on experience in a fast-paced fashion launch

Who You Are:
🖤 Fashion design student or recent graduate
🖤 Obsessed with western wear, pop culture & celebrity style
🖤 Creative, detail-oriented, and ready to hustle
🖤 Available to work from Mumbai (hybrid model)

Perks:
👗 Be part of a brand from the ground up
📸 Opportunities to work on celebrity fittings, lookbooks & campaigns
🌟 A certificate, LOR & future hiring consideration

Duration: 3 months (June–August 2025)
Location: Mumbai
Stipend: Based on experience

⸻

To apply:
Email your resume + portfolio to Team@boltpr.in with the subject line: Design Internship – Western Wear Brand
Deadline for submission: 28th May 2025
